---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Hotkeys" current="hotkeys">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Global Hotkeys</h1>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-10">Trigger any capture mode from anywhere on your Mac with a keyboard shortcut.</p>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Setting a Hotkey</h2>
    <ol class="space-y-2 mb-6">
      {[
        'Open Settings (menu bar → Settings… or ⌘,).',
        'Go to the Hotkeys tab.',
        'Click the key field next to the action you want to configure.',
        'Press your desired key combination.',
        'The shortcut is saved immediately.',
      ].map((s, i) => (
        <li class="flex gap-3 text-sm text-text-secondary">
          <span class="text-accent font-bold flex-shrink-0">{i + 1}.</span> {s}
        </li>
      ))}
    </ol>
    <div class="p-4 border border-yellow-500/20 bg-yellow-500/5 rounded-xl text-sm text-text-secondary">
      <strong class="text-yellow-400">Tip:</strong> Use modifier combinations like ⌃⌘, ⌥⌘, or ⌃⇧ to avoid conflicts with system shortcuts. Reticle hotkeys work even when the app is in the background.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">How Reticle fits alongside macOS</h2>
    <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm mb-4">
      macOS owns <kbd class="bg-black/40 border border-surface-border rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono">⌘⇧3</kbd> and <kbd class="bg-black/40 border border-surface-border rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono">⌘⇧4</kbd> — don't fight it.
      Reticle sits right next to them at <kbd class="bg-black/40 border border-surface-border rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono">⌘⇧2</kbd>.
    </p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-surface-border">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead class="bg-surface-raised border-b border-surface-border">
          <tr>
            <th class="text-left px-5 py-3 text-text-secondary font-medium">Shortcut</th>
            <th class="text-left px-5 py-3 text-text-secondary font-medium">What it does</th>
            <th class="text-left px-5 py-3 text-text-secondary font-medium">Who owns it</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {[
            ['⌘⇧2', 'Region capture with freeze + annotation (Reticle)', 'Reticle'],
            ['⌘⇧3', 'Full-screen → save to Desktop', 'macOS'],
            ['⌘⇧4', 'Region → save to Desktop', 'macOS'],
            ['⌘⇧5', 'Screenshot options panel', 'macOS'],
          ].map(([key, action, owner]) => (
            <tr class="border-b border-surface-border last:border-0">
              <td class="px-5 py-3 font-mono text-sm text-text-primary">{key}</td>
              <td class="px-5 py-3 text-text-secondary">{action}</td>
              <td class={`px-5 py-3 text-xs font-medium ${owner === 'Reticle' ? 'text-accent' : 'text-text-secondary'}`}>{owner}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Default Hotkeys</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-surface-border">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead class="bg-surface-raised border-b border-surface-border">
          <tr>
            <th class="text-left px-5 py-3 text-text-secondary font-medium">Action</th>
            <th class="text-left px-5 py-3 text-text-secondary font-medium">Default</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {[
            ['Capture Region', '⌘⇧2'],
            ['Capture Full Screen', '⌃⌘3'],
            ['Repeat Last Region', '—'],
            ['Clipboard History', '⌘⇧V'],
            ['Color Picker', '—'],
          ].map(([action, key]) => (
            <tr class="border-b border-surface-border last:border-0">
              <td class="px-5 py-3 text-text-secondary">{action}</td>
              <td class="px-5 py-3 font-mono text-sm text-text-primary">{key}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">In-Overlay Shortcuts</h2>
    <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm mb-4">These shortcuts work while the freeze overlay is open:</p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-surface-border">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead class="bg-surface-raised border-b border-surface-border">
          <tr>
            <th class="text-left px-5 py-3 text-text-secondary font-medium">Key</th>
            <th class="text-left px-5 py-3 text-text-secondary font-medium">Action</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {[
            ['⌘Z', 'Undo last annotation'],
            ['Delete / Backspace', 'Delete selected annotation'],
            ['Return / Enter', 'Finalize and capture'],
            ['Escape', 'Cancel capture'],
            ['Shift + drag', 'Constrain to square / 45° angle'],
            ['Shift + click', 'Add to selection (multi-select)'],
          ].map(([key, action]) => (
            <tr class="border-b border-surface-border last:border-0">
              <td class="px-5 py-3 font-mono text-xs text-text-primary">{key}</td>
              <td class="px-5 py-3 text-text-secondary">{action}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Workflow Hotkeys</h2>
    <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">Each Workflow Profile can have its own hotkey that triggers the full capture → annotate → upload pipeline in one press. <a href="/docs/workflows/" class="text-accent hover:underline">See Workflows →</a></p>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
